definitions.definition: (possibly offensive) A girl or young woman, especially a buxom or lively one.
definitions.example: Jane played the role of a wench in an Elizabethan comedy.

definitions.definition: Used as a term of endearment for a female person, especially a wife, daughter, or girlfriend: darling, sweetheart.
A black woman (of any age), especially if in a condition of servitude.
To frequent prostitutes; to whore; also, to womanize.
